<h2>Browser compatibility</h2>
<p>Modern browsers can handle the CSS transitions and animations involved. IE10+, recent Chrome and Firefox support them without prefixes, and Safari requires the <code>-webkit</code> prefix.</p>
<p>Don&#39;t forget to use the prefixed properties within JavaScript too.</p>
